{
  "texts": [
    "To this direction, NPUs capable of running matrix-to-matrix multiplications efficiently with larger onchip cache and memory throughput seems crucial.",
    "The future can also be hybrid [81] and hierarchical, with part of the workload being accelerated at the edge or cloud [56,57,111].Limitations.",
    "Our study is simply the first attempt towards analyzing the on-device behavior of LLM workloads and hope can make them more accessible to the public.",
    "However, our analysis has been limited to chat fine-tuned models of 1-13B parameter size due to their broad availability and popularity.",
    "Very lately, sub-billion models have emerged [65,96], which present their own computational interest in edge settings."
  ]
}